law.text:
With respect to KRS 138.655 to 138.725, it is unlawful for any person to:
Fail to pay the tax imposed;
Fail, neglect, or refuse to file any return in the manner or within the time required;
Make any false statement or conceal any material fact in any record, return, or affidavit;
Conduct any activities requiring a license without such license or after such license has been surrendered, canceled or revoked;
Assign or attempt to assign a license; or
Violate any other provisions.
